body:
### Feature description

What would you think of adding `vim.win` and `vim.buf`?

A bit similar to how you can do `vim.b[buf].comment`

```lua
vim.api.nvim_win_get_option(win, "winhighlight")
vim.api.nvim_buf_line_count(buf)

vim.buf[buf]:line_count()
vim.win[win]:get_option("winhighlight")

local buf = vim.buf[1]
buf:line_count()
buf:set_name("foobar")
```

Instead of `[]`, we could also use `()`.

Just an idea. Makes code shorter and easier to read.

If enough interest and if this is something that would be accepted, I'm willing to create a PR.

## With array access
```lua
local meta = {
  __index = function(_, key)
    return function(self, ...)
      return vim.api[("nvim_%s_%s"):format(self.type, key)](self[self.type], ...)
    end
  end,
}

vim.buf = setmetatable({}, {
  __index = function(_, buf)
    buf = buf == 0 and vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()
    return setmetatable({ type = "buf", buf = buf }, meta)
  end,
})

vim.win = setmetatable({}, {
  __index = function(_, win)
    win = win == 0 and vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()
    return setmetatable({ type = "win", win = win }, meta)
  end,
})

local buf = vim.buf[0]

print(buf:line_count())

buf:set_name("foobar")

print(buf:get_name())
```

## As functions

```lua
local meta = {
  __index = function(_, key)
    return function(self, ...)
      return vim.api[("nvim_%s_%s"):format(self.type, key)](self[self.type], ...)
    end
  end,
}

---@param buf? number Buffer or 0 for the current buffer
function vim.buf(buf)
  buf = buf and buf ~= 0 and buf or vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()
  return setmetatable({ type = "buf", buf = buf }, meta)
end

---@param win? number Window or 0 for the current window
function vim.win(win)
  win = win and win ~= 0 and win or vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()
  return setmetatable({ type = "win", win = win }, meta)
end

local buf = vim.buf()

print(buf:line_count())

buf:set_name("foobar")

print(buf:get_name())
```
